{
  "text": "ALH was greater in Tris-cEY and Optixcell\u00ae than in a Bioxcell\u00ae, which is in contrast with a preceding report held by [CITATION_1] . Overall, greater values of VCL with ALH is not desired (ALH \u2265 7\u00b5m, VCL \u2265 70\u00b5m), because it indicate hyper-activated sperms (Kathidravan et al., 2011) . Moreover, according to [CITATION_2] , a higher value of ALH indicates inferior quality of sperm and can disturb the cell cycle progression.",
